to get me to chase it.

20:33.144 --> 20:35.513
Just like in that
famous movie, right?

20:35.513 --> 20:37.098
Uh-huh.

20:37.098 --> 20:41.102
And he ends up flat
on his back in bed,
on valentine's day,

20:41.102 --> 20:43.104
just like in high school.

20:43.104 --> 20:44.438
[sighing]

20:44.438 --> 20:46.907
you know, you could write
that story down,

20:46.907 --> 20:49.910
.
put fabio on the cover
and sell it at the airport

20:49.910 --> 20:52.947
that is one of
the sweetest stories.

20:53.948 --> 20:54.949
Nancy,

20:55.449 --> 20:56.450
could I--

20:56.450 --> 20:59.286
Could I borrow
your cell phone
for a moment?

21:01.205 --> 21:03.207
[ringing]

21:03.207 --> 21:04.425
[sighing]

21:05.009 --> 21:05.793
hello.

21:06.293 --> 21:08.596
(peggy)
hello, Mr. Hill.
This is Miss platter.

21:08.596 --> 21:09.930
oh.

21:09.930 --> 21:12.716
Well, good evenin'
, Miss platter.

21:12.716 --> 21:16.053
Uh, to what do I owe
the pleasure of this call?

21:16.053 --> 21:18.055
